**STEP 2: CHOOSE YOUR ESCAPE ROUTE**

**Route A: Content Export (Best Case)**
- Export all content via platform tools
- Export images manually (screenshot/download)
- Rebuild on new platform using exported content
- **Timeline:** 2-4 weeks
- **Cost:** $0-5,000 (DIY vs professional)

**Route B: Manual Rebuild (Common)**
- Copy all text content manually
- Download all images from live site
- Document page structure
- Rebuild from scratch on new platform
- **Timeline:** 4-8 weeks
- **Cost:** $2,000-15,000

**Route C: Professional Migration (Expensive)**
- Hire agency specializing in migrations
- They handle content export and rebuild
- Test thoroughly before going live
- **Timeline:** 2-6 weeks
- **Cost:** $5,000-25,000

**STEP 3: MIGRATE CAREFULLY**
- Set up new platform in parallel (don't cancel old yet)
- Transfer domain (start 60 days before canceling)
- Set up 301 redirects for SEO
- Test thoroughly on new platform
- Keep old site live until new is perfect
- Update DNS only when ready
- Monitor for 30 days after migration

